jobs

Class Job

  • java.lang.Object
    • jobs.Job

  • @Immutable
public final class Job
extends Object
    Job is an immutable data class that represent a task. Each task is characterize with it's Starting date, Due date, Duration and Id.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Job

        public Job(int est,
           int lct,
           int p,
           int i)
    throws JobEndbeforeStartException,
           JobInvalidDurationException,
           JobInvalidRankException,
           JobNegativeException
        Job constructor.
        Parameters:
        est - Earliest starting time.
        lct - Last completion time. Note that lct is not exclusive as it use to be in scheduling problem convention.
        p - Duration.
        i - Id.
        Throws:
        JobEndbeforeStartException - The job end before it's start.
        JobInvalidDurationException - The duration does not fit in the time window.
        JobInvalidRankException - The rank is lower than 0.
        JobNegativeException - Some input are negative.
